{"id": "EUVD-2023-60391", "enisaUuid": "3ebe64b4-3035-302f-b918-c642f659dce2", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nksmbd: avoid out of bounds access in decode_preauth_ctxt()\n\nConfirm that the accessed pneg_ctxt->HashAlgorithms address sits within\nthe SMB request boundary; deassemble_neg_contexts() only checks that the\neight byte smb2_neg_context header + (client controlled) DataLength are\nwithin the packet boundary, which is insufficient.\n\nChecking for sizeof(struct smb2_preauth_neg_context) is overkill given\nthat the type currently assumes SMB311_SALT_SIZE bytes of trailing Salt.", "datePublished": "2025-12-30T12:15:47", "dateUpdated": "2026-01-05T11:37:04", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/39f5b4b313b445c980a2a295bed28228c29228ed", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/a2f6ded41bec1d3be643c80a5eb97f1680309001", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/f02edb9debbd36f44efa7567031485892c7df60d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e7067a446264a7514fa1cfaa4052cdb6803bc6a2", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2023-54250"], "aliases": ["CVE-2023-54250"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "10df23c7-49fc-3bc2-92a2-5755953f858f", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <e7067a446264a7514fa1cfaa4052cdb6803bc6a2"}, {"id": "22f05e80-c68a-3a57-af68-26b009785885", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "e2f34481b24db2fd634b5edb0a5bd0e4d38cc6e9 <a2f6ded41bec1d3be643c80a5eb97f1680309001"}, {"id": "4cbc729e-efca-391e-9258-ab459a6f6995", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <a2f6ded41bec1d3be643c80a5eb97f1680309001"}, {"id": "50a9cef6-60cf-38e6-b734-b52917be8a34", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "6d6eaf2a-68af-3cdb-ae93-3a1c0778fc2b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "5.15"}, {"id": "76e48489-a46d-3c17-a694-f161